    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="748"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 212.11G16/2.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 42.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Pursuant to the department’s telegraphic
                    instruction of April 14,<note n="1" xml:id="d748fn1">Not printed.</note> of the
                    14th instant, received to-day, I have the honor to report that I have requested
                    the provisional arrest and detention of Jacinto Garcia and Heliodoro Garcia,
                    charged with murder in California, who are supposed to be at Camargo, Chihuahua,
                    and Jalostotitlan, Jalisco.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
